{"nodeA": 2, "nodeB": 4, "synthesis": "Paxos flexible quorums (R+W>N) could be implemented atop a knowledge graph that encodes quorum configurations as typed relationships between server nodes, enabling multi-hop reasoning about which quorum sets remain valid under specific failure scenarios — something that flat configuration tables cannot support. This would allow a consensus system to dynamically reason about its own quorum availability.", "pattern": "structure-enables-reasoning"}